   Newsroom

   30 September 2019
   EBS Intern Views - Interview with Martin Stöckel

   In our series #EBSInternViews, we provide insights into the internships
   our students have completed during their semester break. Martin Stöckel
   talks about his experiences at UniCredit in Munich, a German credit
   institution.
   27 September 2019
   Thirtieth EBS Symposium in Oestrich-Winkel

   From 18 to 20 September 2019, the 30th EBS Symposium, one of the
   largest student-run business congresses in Germany, was all about the
   topic “Breaking Barriers. Challenge your tomorrow”. As patron, Dr.
   Joachim Faber, Chairman of the Supervisory Board of Deutsche Börse,
   welcomed the around 850 participants to the campus of EBS Universität
   für Wirtschaft und Recht in Oestrich-Winkel.
   27 September 2019
   Start-up: Macakao

   In this series, we present start-ups our EBS Alumni founded. MBA
   graduate José Miguel Rodriguez Damiani and his partner Maximilian Ott
   founded the start-up Kallpa Superfoods, which distributes the product
   Macakao. Macakao? Learn more about the product in this interview. We
   can reveal: it will be delicious!
   to the newsroom of EBS

